      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add WhatsApp read-only mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a true read-only mode for WhatsApp channels so OpenClaw can ingest and analyze inbound WhatsApp messages without ever sending outbound WhatsApp traffic.\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#71166.\n\n## Problem\n\nWhatsApp could emit automatic outbound messages during inbound handling, including access-not-configured notices, pairing prompts, replies, read receipts, reactions, polls, typing indicators, and other transport-level sends.\n\nThat made it unsafe to attach WhatsApp in observation-only or production-adjacent setups, because there was no hard configuration-level guarantee that OpenClaw would stay silent.\n\n## Fix\n\nThis PR adds `readOnly: true` support for WhatsApp at both channel and per-account config scopes, then enforces it inside the WhatsApp transport as a hard outbound gate.\n\nWhen enabled, WhatsApp still receives and processes inbound messages, but outbound actions are dropped before they can leave the system.\n\nCovered outbound paths include:\n\n- text and media sends\n- polls\n- reactions\n- typing/composing indicators\n- inbound reply/send API closures\n- pairing replies\n- read receipts\n- connect presence\n\n## Testing\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions --pretty false`\n- Targeted WhatsApp tests: 4 files, 48 tests\n\n## Notes\n\nThis is intentionally enforced at the transport layer so accidental replies from agents, default system notices, or edge-case error handling cannot bypass read-only mode.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-71166",
